{"_id":"24DXUzhohbDVrP15","name":"Ruins of Gobol Karn","content":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops:right 8.0in\"><span class=\"RPGMaterial\"><span style=\"mso-ansi-font-size:12.0pt\">Gobol Karn, the ancient goblin empire, once rivalled the Auran Empire, Caras Seidharen, and Gjalerbron, the three empires of the east. It fell before they did, however, falling apart under the weight of a rigid caste system, inbreeding among the aristocracy, and a well-timed slave uprising. The territory Gobol Karn once occupied—now part of the Unclaimed Reaches—is now home to debased goblin tribes, not even a shadow of their former glory, but the ruins still hold valuable secrets. The ancient goblins worked wonders with alchemy, and every few years an expedition brings back some rediscovered formula, or strange creatures escaped from the laboratories of Gobol Karn’s alchemical breeders. However, most expeditions return empty-handed, or not at all...</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops:right 8.0in\">Downriver from the ruins, the town of Nygolb is home to the Gobol Reclamation League, an effort to re-establish a goblin homeland spearheaded by a handful of boggart collectives on behalf of their goblin cousins. While on the surface Nygolb is a refreshingly civilized and orderly town for the Reaches, there have been enough mysterious deaths and disappearances that the town has developed an unsavory reputation. The League is undoubtedly spreading a civilizing influence throughout the nearby goblin tribes, but it would appear that there is also a hidden agenda in play...</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":2,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3,"lh2XdhvmO8rwUMvb":2},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.aetrimonde_v0_8_x.aetrimonde-setting.24DXUzhohbDVrP15"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jtqi9qh2rjq","path":"The World of Aetrimonde#/CF_SEP/Unincorporated Territories","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"2i2UlFIy3OM2mRc5","name":"Urku","content":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops:right 8.0in\"><span class=\"RPGMaterial\"><span style=\"mso-ansi-font-size:12.0pt\">The snowy home of the orcs is largely unexplored by outsiders. Tribal orcs are widely feared by outsiders, having been the cause of the Collapse, and nobody wants to see those events repeated—least of all the orcs themselves. The orcs of Urku are descended from those who stayed behind and did not join the horde that caused the Collapse. Far from being the bloodthirsty monsters of legend, these orcs purposefully isolate themselves from outsiders in an effort to avoid a repeat of the Collapse, which killed most of a generation of young orcs. Their borderlands are inhabited by outcasts: orcs unable or unwilling to be anything but a blood-soaked monster. These violent savages serve as a deterrent to outsiders, but past them, the shamanic orcs of Urku practice rigid self-control, venting their fury only in ritualized, nonlethal duels or by hunting dangerous beasts. </span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops:right 8.0in\"><span class=\"RPGMaterial\"><span style=\"mso-ansi-font-size:12.0pt\">The city of Urku is located in a dense, subarctic forest: the cold and the rough terrain deter most visitors, as does the fact that Urku's location on most maps is only approximate. Urku is purposefully designed to be the orc tribes' stronghold: it is located on a vast terraced mound raised by generations of orc hands, and the earthworks are both fortification and farmland. Most of the arable land within the earthworks lies fallow, but if it were worked (especially with the assistance of druidic magic to deal with the cool growing season), it would be more than enough to feed the entirety of the local tribes. The intent of the builders and planners is that, if war ever came to Urku, they could withdraw into this unassailable stronghold while the warlike outcasts sated their bloodlust.</span></span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":2,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3,"lh2XdhvmO8rwUMvb":2},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.aetrimonde_v0_8_x.aetrimonde-setting.2i2UlFIy3OM2mRc5"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w4yki4y5ebj","path":"The World of Aetrimonde#/CF_SEP/Minor Polities","color":"#000000"}}}
